<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51100">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51100">
The collected specimen was a juvenile male measuring 330 mm in total length, 160 mm in disc length and 188 mm in disc width and weighing 171.8 g (total weight). Additionally, twenty six morphological characters were also recorded (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T5649913" captionText="Table 1. Morphological characters of D. marmorata from Maliakos Gulf, Greece and percentages against disc width (DW), following previously proposed biometric measurements. The total and eviscerated weight of the animal are also included in grams (g)." pageId="0" pageNumber="51100">1</tableCitation>
) following biometric measurements from recent studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Psomadakis, P. N." journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiveristy Records" pageId="0" pageNumber="51100" refId="B5669239" refString="Psomadakis, P. N., Dalu, M., Scacco, U., Vacchi, M., 2008. A rare batoid fish Gymnura altavela (Chondrichthyes: Gymnuridae) captured in the Tyrrhenian Sea. Marine Biodiveristy Records 1, E6" title="A rare batoid fish Gymnura altavela (Chondrichthyes: Gymnuridae) captured in the Tyrrhenian Sea." volume="1, E 6" year="2008">Psomadakis et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, W. D." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Fish Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="51100" pagination="761 - 783" refId="B5676434" refString="Smith, W. D., Bizzarro, J. J., Richards, V. P., Nielsen, J., Marquez -Farias, F., Shivji, M. S., 2009. Morphometric convergence and molecular divergence: the taxonomic status and evolutionary history of Gymnura crebripunctata and Gymnura marmorata in the eastern Pacific Ocean. Journal of Fish Biology 75 (4): 761 - 783" title="Morphometric convergence and molecular divergence: the taxonomic status and evolutionary history of Gymnura crebripunctata and Gymnura marmorata in the eastern Pacific Ocean" volume="75" year="2009">Smith et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
